        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 6:44PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 642 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
between Peaks Of Otter Summit and Bedford, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail. Very Heavy Rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bedford...
Big Island...
Coleman Falls...
Snowden...
Peaks Of Otter Summit...
Peaks Of Otter Recreation Area...
and Sedalia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
